  "prompt": "Which US Senate seats are up for reelection in 2018?",
  "response": "In 2018, 35 U.S. Senate seats were up for reelection. This included 26 seats held by Democrats and 9 seats held by Republicans. Notable seats included those held by Democratic Senators in states that voted for Donald Trump in the 2016 presidential election, such as Joe Manchin (West Virginia), Heidi Heitkamp (North Dakota), and Claire McCaskill (Missouri). Additionally, Republican seats, such as those held by Jeff Flake (Arizona) and Dean Heller (Nevada), were also closely watched. The election resulted in the Republican Party maintaining control of the Senate.",
